 Pray send me, in the course of the day, if possible, twelve copies of the Pictures from Italy.<note><hi rend="italic">Pictures from Italy</hi> was first published in the <hi rend="italic">Daily News</hi> between 21 January and 11 March 1846, then as a single volume in May 1846, with illustrations by Samuel Palmer. Bradbury &amp; Evans's Accounts show that CD was sent 25 copies in total; see <hi rend="italic">To</hi> Felix Joyce, 19 May 1846, in Pilgrim <hi rend="italic">Letters</hi> 4, p. 547.</note>
